Police are investigating a mob justice incident in Eldorado park following an attack on two men accused of abducting a young girl. The community accused the men for attempting to put a young girl into a trolley they used to collect second-hand goods. The police said the pair was taken to a nearby hospital for urgent medical attention. Police spokesperson Kay Makhubela said two community members have been brought in for questioning, and one has been charged for public violence. “The community members proceeded to the police station where to burn tyres, however, we were able to disperse them.” He said the police has not received any reports of a missing person yet but more investigations are conducted. Makhubela added that the police are monitoring the two men in hospital and will take their statements when they are fit.  -TNA Reporter  